            <div class="comment_body">
                                                                                                                
                This does sound good! I have both smoked and fried turkeys in the past. While I prefer smoked for many reasons, the advantage to frying them is a ridiculous<wbr/>&shy;ly quick cook time and the crispy skin that results. When I'm preparing the turkey at 8am to take to the family feast at 1, frying is simply the quickest option for a fresh turkey. Regardless of the cooking method, the brine and (in my case) injection are the crucial parts to keeping the bird moist and flavorful. A turkey not brined is of no interest to me or my taste buds.            </div>
            
