                As of last year, I became a fan of the high-temp method where the turkey cooks at 450 or 500 for a very short time. It is remarkably delicious, stays incredibly juicy. I thought it beat out the deep fried turkeys my family has been hooked on for the last five years by leaps and bounds. I just couldn't believe the rich flavor it produced.            </div>
            
