            <div class="comment_body">
                                                                                                                
                The bird, or any cut of meat, is roasted at the high temp for just a short time.  This method creates a crust on the outside that keeps juices in.  Then, lower the temp to allow it to cook through.  <br />
<br />
I've roasted meats this way for forty years.  It works.<br />
<br />
I really enjoy your recipes.  You care about what you do and it shows.            </div>
            
