            <div class="comment_body">
                                                                                                                
                Definitely<wbr/>&shy;, I keep the turkey between 14 and 16 lbs. I use my thermomete<wbr/>&shy;r to make sure the breasts are up to temp before I call it done. I am definitely going to try your recipe as so far you have not steered me wrong. In fact, the grilled yams (just kidding--s<wbr/>&shy;weet potatoes) are on the menu as my contributi<wbr/>&shy;on to the meal next week. However, I have to say, the high temp method really produces a juicy and flavorful bird, and the outside so far has never gotten overdone.<br />
<br />
Obviously a lot of the draw to this method is the speed, but I swear to you, it is delicious.<br />
<br />
I would love to know your thoughts on roasting boneless turkey roasts so they can be sliced thin for sandwiches<wbr/>&shy;. That's been a challenge for me and so far unsuccessf<wbr/>&shy;ul.            </div>
            
